cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a meta-learning system for recommending the best predictive method for a given multi-target regression problem. This involves exploring inter-target correlation within the problem and evaluating four different algorithms with different biases as meta-learners. The paper also uses a meta-dataset composed of 58 meta-features based on statistical information, correlation characteristics, linear landmarking, from the distribution and smoothness of the data, and has four different meta-labels. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
